<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<aiml>

  <category>
    <pattern>hello</pattern>
    <patter>hi</patter>
    <template>
      Hello! I am a chatbot designed to help narrow down potential computing careers you might be interested in! When communicating with me, 
      please try to only respond via the bolded terms, otherwise I might not recognize what you're saying. To start, please tell me your name. 
      Start with like this, <b>my name is...</b></template>
  </category>
  
  <category>
      <pattern>*</pattern>
      <template>I have no answer for that, you can reset the chatbot by either saying My name is....</template>
  </category>
  
  <category>
      <pattern>my name is *</pattern>
      <template>Hello <star/>! Let's see if I could try and narrow some computing jobs down. 
          Do you prefer jobs involving:<br></br> <b>design</b> or <b>analysis?</b></template>
  </category>
  
 <!-- branch off into design or analytical jobs-->
  
  <category>
      <pattern>design</pattern>
      <template>Design related jobs are fun! Are you more specifically more interested in designing either:<br></br> <b>software</b> or <b>an interface</b></template>
  </category>
  
  <category>
      <pattern>analysis</pattern>
      <template>Analysis related jobs are a good choice. Do you prefer analyzing:<br></br> <b>data</b> or <b>cybersecurity</b></template>
  </category>
  
  <!--design jobs-->
  
  <category>
      <pattern>an interface</pattern>
      <patter>interface</patter>
      <template>Designing an interface requires a great deal of creativity in addition to programming knowledge!
      Do you think you would prefer creating an interface for something made:<br></br> <b>online</b> or <b>in an application?</b></template>
  </category>
  
  <category>
      <pattern>an application</pattern>
      <pattern>in an application</pattern>
      <pattern>application</pattern>
      <template>So you would like designing interfaces within an independent application! Sounds like to me you would be most interested in becoming a UI Designer (User-inferface)! 
      Being a UI designer entails creating a human-friendly, readable interface for various applications. </template>
  </category>
  
  
  <category>
      <pattern>online</pattern>
      <template>So you would like designing an interface for a website. Sounds like you would be most interested in becoming a web designer!
      Being a web designer use their creative skills to create attention grabbing, functional websites for companies!</template>
  </category>
 
 <!-- end response for software, data, and cybersecurity-->
 
  <category>
      <pattern>software</pattern>
      <template>Given your interests in designing software, I think your best fitting career would be that of a software engineer!
      That occupation involves the design, testing, and maintenance of applications to ensure that they are functional for public use!</template>
  </category>
  
  <category>
      <pattern>cybersecurity</pattern>
      <template>Given your interests in analyzing aspects related to cybersecurity, you would probably enjoy being a cybersecurity analyst! That occupation
      involves the analysis and implementation of security measures to protect company data from outside factors.</template>
  </category>
  
  <category>
      <pattern>data</pattern>
      <template>Given your interests in analyzing data, I believe you would enjoy being a data analyst! That job involves the usage of strategies such as
      surveys and web traffic to create datasets that could be analyzed for the benefit of a company!</template>
  </category>
  
  
  
</aiml>
